04696nam a22006615i 9780292794658DE-B159720211129102213.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211129t20212007txu    fo  d z      eng d  a97802927946587 a10.7560/7146562doi  a(DE-B1597)587775  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  atxucUS-TX 7aPER0000002bisacsh04a791.43/7222200aThelma & Louise Live! :bThe Cultural Afterlife of an American Film /ced. by Bernie Cook. 1aAustin : bUniversity of Texas Press, c[2021] 4c©2007  a1 online resource (240 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tACKNOWLEDGMENTS -- tINTRODUCTION “I Can See Clearly Now” -- t1 “SOMETHING’S CROSSED OVER IN ME” New Ways of Seeing Thelma & Louise -- t2 GETTING HYSTERICAL Thelma & Louise and Laughter -- t3 HEARING THELMA & LOUISE Active Reading of the Hybrid Pop Score -- t4 INTERPLAYING IDENTITIES Acting and the Building Blocks of Character in Thelma & Louise -- t5 AN OUTLAW-COUPLE-ON-THE-RUN FILM FOR THE 1990S -- t6 “WHAT ALL THE FUSS IS ABOUT” Making Brad Pitt in Thelma & Louise -- t7 INTERVIEW WITH CALLIE KHOURI December 19, 2002 -- tAPPENDIX I Commentaries -- tAPPENDIX II Filmographies -- tSELECTED BIBLIOGRAPHY -- tCONTRIBUTORS -- tINDEX0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aWhen they floored their Thunderbird off a cliff rather than surrender to the law, Thelma and Louise became icons of female rebellion, provoking strong reactions from viewers who felt either empowered or outraged by the duo's transgressions of women's traditional roles. The 1991 film quickly became—and continues to be—a potent cultural reference point, even inspiring a bumper sticker that declares, "Thelma & Louise Live!" In this insightful study of Thelma & Louise, six noted film scholars investigate the initial reception and ongoing impact of this landmark film. The writers consider Thelma & Louise from a variety of perspectives, turning attention to the film's promotion and audience response over time; to theories of comedy and the role of laughter in the film; to the film's soundtrack and score; to the performances of stars Susan Sarandon and Geena Davis; to the emergence of Brad Pitt as a star and male sex object; and to the film's place in the history of road and crime film genres. Complementing the scholarly analysis is an in-depth interview of screenwriter Callie Khouri by editor Bernie Cook, as well as reviews of Thelma & Louise that appeared in U.S. News & World Report and Time. Offering myriad new ways of understanding the complex interrelations of gender, identity, and violence, Thelma & Louise Live! attests to the ongoing life and still-evolving meanings of this now-classic film.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh1 aCook, Bernie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCook, Bernie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFuchs, Cynthia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGorbman, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKnobloch, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeo, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSlocum, J. David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSturtevant, Victoria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292794658423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292794658/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aP